  "texts": [
    "Among the competing strategies, MFMES exhibits remarkable outcomes in terms of convergence values of the errors when all the library of fidelities is available.",
    "This results can be justified with the over-exploration properties of the MFMES acquisition function: the learner uses massive low-fidelity data to refine the approximation of the surrogate model and augment its predictive capabilities.",
    "This permits to better inform the procedure and direct computational resources toward the optimum.The results obtained for the ALOS benchmark problem in Fig. 13 confirm the previous observations about the different effectiveness of the learning schemes.",
    "In particular, the multifidelity strategies provides larger accelerations of the optimization procedure in presence oscillations at different frequencies of the objective function for the one-(Fig. 13a, d), two-(Fig.",
    "13b, e) and three-(Fig. 13c, f) dimensional ALOS problem."
